<br>
Idiots Who Sue Over Everything and Anything! (My thoughts are mostly on medical malpractice.)<br>
<br>
Well, my thoughts were brought to this subject today by my uncle telling us at dinner about a 300 pound diabetic with heart disease. She had a stroke, and the doctors spent a month to save her life. In the end, she would be confined to a wheelchair for the rest of her life. So, when she has the first chance, she turns around and sues those who worked so diligently to save her. In the end, a jury full of people too stupid to get out of jury duty decide to award her $6 million ($1 million in medical costs, $5 million in &quot;pain and suffering&quot;), her reason for suing being, &quot;they weren't miracle workers who could make me perfectly healthy again.&quot;<br>
<br>
Now, I would just like to go on a tyraid for a bit. I HATE &quot;pain and suffering.&quot; The thing about it is, you CAN'T PUT A PRICE ON PAIN! So, given the chance, people sueing will go for the largest sum possible, and the government hasn't done a thing to regulate the amounts awarded for pain and suffering, so people can get $5 million (and even more) for pain, and yet the government has done nothing to regulate it, making malpractice insurance rates go up! JEESE!<br>
<br>
So anyway, how can people be so stupid? I mean, these doctors are doing their best to save the lives of those they treat (well, most of them.) But in the end, doctors are still people! But, people believe that doctors are miracle workers, who can bring people back from the dead and turn water to wine, and when they find that their loved one is dead or incapacitated, they think it's DELIBERATE, and they MUST BE PUNISHED!<br>
<br>
Well, the thing is, there are bad doctors practicing, who do deserve to have suits brought against them, but little seems to be done about them.<br>
<br>
So anyway, when this happens, and a jury full of high school dropouts who still work at Popeye's and still have about 10 children apiece hear these stories (of course, made into a heartbreaking tale of horrible neglect by the lawyers), they decide, &quot;Hey, this is a bunch of self-important doctors stiffing it to the little guy! Lets take them for all they are worth! And then go buy porno with our $9 a day!&quot; <br>
<br>
So then, these honorable doctor's malpractice insurance rates shoot up, and they could possibly end up leaving the state or medicine alltogether. <br>
<br>
Some day, when our medical people are even more low in number than they are now because of the risks of some idiot selfishly destroying their livelihood, we'll look back and say, &quot;Hey! We shouldn't have done this!&quot;<br>
<br>
And then we'll sue ourselves.<br>
